HEADWORD: Segregation
<hw>Seg`re*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>segregatio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧gr⟦eacute⟧gation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
segregating, or the state of being segregated; separation from others; a
parting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Separation from a mass, and
gathering about centers or into cavities at hand through cohesive
attraction or the crystallizing process.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seiches</ent>⟦br⟧
